reviews.review_text: My 77th Show This is one of the greatest Dead shows I ever saw. This whole run was full of cool jams and interesting song choices. It was 1990 & the boys were playing strong. I consider this run, and particularly this night, as the unofficial 25th Anniversary shows. The band officially releasing this in their View From The Vault series somewhat vindicates my opinion. I feel like they made a point of changing things up (eg. Truckin’ as the second song) and stretching things out (China/Rider jam). These would be my last Brent shows. Being a keyboardist and B-3 player, it was a pretty devastating loss. But enough of that. I just love this show. I had pretty good seats (thanks E) and I’m remember at the time being mesmerized during that post-Terrapin jam where everyone stayed onstage (almost) the whole time. I’d never seen anything like that before or since (I got on the bus in ‘84). Their energy and sense of adventure was electric. We are so lucky to have this resource to go back and listen to these shows.
